Upon further investigation, I found that the Central upgrade is blocked because it is unable to create the central-db-backup PVC due to storage quota limits in the stackrox namespace.

The error in the Central CR indicates that the new backup PVC request is being denied because the namespace quota is exceeded.

Could you please confirm the recommended and supported approach for this situation in production?

Specifically:
	•	Is increasing the stackrox namespace storage quota the correct next step?
	•	After increasing the quota, will the operator automatically resume and complete the Central upgrade from 4.7.3 to 4.10.1?
	•	If not, what exact post-quota actions should we take to successfully complete the upgrade?
	•	Are there any additional validation or recovery steps you recommend after quota is increased?

Please advise on the safest supported steps to complete the Central upgrade successfully.
